
[1]pilfering

   PIL'FERING, pp. Stealing; practicing petty thefts.

   PIL'FERING, n. Petty theft.

   Pilfering was so universal in all the South sea islands, that it was
   hardly recognized in the moral code of the natives as an offense, much
   less a crime.
